==English==
===Etymology===
Named for the discoverer, [[w:Akira Suzuki|Akira Suzuki]].

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|sg=[[Suzuki]] [[reaction]]}}
# {{chemistry}} The [[organic]] reaction of an [[aryl]]- or [[vinyl]]-[[boronic acid]] with an aryl- or vinyl-[[halide]] or [[pseudohalide]], such as [[triflate]]s, catalyzed by a [[palladium]](0) [[complex]], widely used to [[synthesize]] [[polyolefin]]s, [[styrene]]s, and substituted [[biphenyl]]s.

